                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On a detached stone built into the outer <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Parāntaka I. Year [3]2: 938-39 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription dated in the reign of Maduraikoṇḍa Parakēsari i.e., Parāntaka I. seems to record a gift to god Tiruvēṅgaḍattu niṉṟaruḷiṉa Perumāṉaḍigaḷ by the king, Śrī Pirāntaka. </p>						
                            
